    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Encode categorical features\n",
        "data_encoded = pd.get_dummies(data, drop_first=True)"

      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Feature Engineering (Updated columns based on get_dummies output)\n",
        "possible_services = [\n",
        "    'PhoneService_Yes',\n",
        "    'MultipleLines_Yes',\n",
        "    'InternetService_Fiber optic',\n",
        "    'OnlineSecurity_No',\n",
        "    'OnlineBackup_No',\n",
        "    'DeviceProtection_No',\n",
        "    'TechSupport_No',\n",
        "    'StreamingTV_No',\n",
        "    'StreamingMovies_No'\n",
        "]"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "nyQ2Sl5EEnJi"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "for col in possible_services:\n",
        "    if col not in data_encoded.columns:\n",
        "        print(f\"Missing expected column: {col}\")"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "bNmrRPOJEtip",
        "outputId": "fdf496c6-261d-4f57-f7a1-945b1b256891"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Missing expected column: OnlineSecurity_No\n",
            "Missing expected column: OnlineBackup_No\n",
            "Missing expected column: DeviceProtection_No\n",
            "Missing expected column: TechSupport_No\n",
            "Missing expected column: StreamingTV_No\n",
            "Missing expected column: StreamingMovies_No\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Create new feature based on available columns\n",
        "available_services = [col for col in possible_services if col in data_encoded.columns]\n",
        "data_encoded['TotalServicesUsed'] = data_encoded[available_services].sum(axis=1)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "q8ozvbSEE1ZR"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Split features and target\n",
        "X = data_encoded.drop('Churn', axis=1)\n",
        "y = data_encoded['Churn']\n",
        "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, stratify=y, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "-m3WHBe_E6Ox"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Scale numeric features\n",
        "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
        "X_train = scaler.fit_transform(X_train)\n",
        "X_test = scaler.transform(X_test)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "jXw7NYMEE9yk"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Models\n",
        "models = {\n",
        "    'Logistic Regression': LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000),\n",
        "    'Random Forest': RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100),\n",
        "    'XGBoost': XGBClassifier(use_label_encoder=False, eval_metric='logloss')\n",
        "}"

      "metadata": {
        "id": "8--uPrA4FKhU"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "\n",
        "from imblearn.over_sampling import SMOTE\n",
        "X = data.drop('Churn', axis=1)\n",
        "y = data['Churn']\n",
        "\n",
        "# Feature Scaling\n",
        "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
        "X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Handle class imbalance with SMOTE\n",
        "smote = SMOTE(random_state=42)\n",
        "X_resampled, y_resampled = smote.fit_resample(X_scaled, y)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Train/Test Split\n",
        "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X_resampled, y_resampled, test_size=0.2, random_state=42, stratify=y_resampled)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "uomeb8WxGmKQ"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# XGBoost Model with tuned parameters\n",
        "xgb = XGBClassifier(\n",
        "    learning_rate=0.1,\n",
        "    max_depth=6,\n",
        "    n_estimators=200,\n",
        "    subsample=0.8,\n",
        "    colsample_bytree=0.8,\n",
        "    use_label_encoder=False,\n",
        "    eval_metric='logloss',\n",
        "    random_state=42\n",
        ")"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "412eq6hnH2aG"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Train & Predict\n",
        "xgb.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "y_pred = xgb.predict(X_test)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Evaluation\n",
        "print(\"\\nXGBoost Classifier with Tuning and SMOTE:\")\n",
        "print(\"Accuracy:\", accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))\n",
        "print(\"Classification Report:\\n\", classification_report(y_test, y_pred))"
      ],
      "metadata": {
